1 ggplot2

first 3 layer are essential, others are optional 

ggplot(data, aes())+layer(geom,
                          geom_params, 
                          stats, 
                          stats_params,
                          data, 
                          mapping, 
                          position)
  • every layer can be specified on its own
  • by using ggplot you can add several layers to your plot
  • a layer overrides the existing one (e.g. data can be added for a layer)
  • note that quite often the inital plot is stored as p
  • some available geoms: histogram, jitter, area, density, quantile, smooth, freqplot
  • note that some geoms mean the same e.g. bar and histogram “aliased”

stats are statistical transformations (bins, smooth, density, errorbars, quantile, summary)

position makes adjustemts to the location # (doge, fill, jitter, stack, identity)
